  "title": "Engineer - Projects",
  "description": "<p>The Candidate should be able to perform the following tasks,<br /></p><p>· To monitor the installation progress as well as coordinate with Clients, Consultants, Subcontractors to ensure efficient and timely delivery of assignments.</p><p>. Proficiency in BMS/BAS/ ELEC platforms, SCADA integration and data-driven energy analysis.</p><p>. PLC, DDC Programming.</p><p>· To report and monitor the progress of the project to the Project Manager.</p><p>· To supervise and ensure works are in accordance with the contract drawings and specifications.</p><p>· To prepare method statements, shop drawings, installations / T&C check sheets, work progress reports, and other relevant documents for M&E-related works with project teams.</p><p>· To coordinate with subcontractors and consultants on preparation and submission of shop drawings.</p><p>· To assist the Project Manager to negotiate/procuring materials, equipment, and labor in accordance with (or below) the allocated approved budget.</p><p>· To hold technical discussions with various stakeholders to resolve technical / site issues.</p><p>· To have experience in working at Data Centre.</p><p>· Mechanical: Familiar with VAV / VRV / cooling tower / Chillers / chilled water pipe / A&A works.</p><p>· Electrical: Familiar with retrofit / renovation / lighting control / BMS<br /></p><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><p>The candidate should also be experienced with the following.</p><p>· Building Automation Systems (Extra Low Voltage (ELV)</p><p>· Navisworks</p><p>· Knowledge on Revit will be an added advantage</p><p>· Microsoft Office</p>",
